\b\i0\f0\fs32 13.What are the ways to integrate CSS as a web page?\par
\b0\i\fs24 1).Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements.\par
2).Internal - by using a <style> element in the <head> section.\par
3).External - by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file.\par
\par
\b\i0\fs28 14.What is embedded style sheets? \par
\b0\i\fs24 It allows you to define styles for a particular HTML document as a whole in one place. This is done by embedding the <style></style> tags containing the CSS properties in the head of your document. \par
Embedded style sheets are particularly useful for HTML documents that have unique style requirements from the rest of the documents in your project. However, if the styles need to be applied across multiple documents, you should link to an external style sheet instead of using individual embedded style sheets. Using embedded stylesheets holds a distinct advantage over inline styles which only allow you to address one HTML element at a time. \par
\b\fs32\par
\i0 15.What are the external style sheets? \par
\b0\i\fs24 An external style sheet is a separate CSS file that can be accessed by creating a link within the head section of the webpage. Multiple webpages can use the same link to access the stylesheet.\par
The link to an external style sheet is placed within the head section of the page.It uses the <link> tag on every pages and the <link> tag should be put inside the head section\par
\par
\b\i0\fs32 16.What are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheets?\par
\b0\i\fs24 The advantages of External Style Sheets are:\par
- Using them, the styles of multiple documents can be controlled from one file.\par
- Classes can be created for use on multiple HTML element types in many documents.\par
- In complex situations, selector and grouping methods can be used to apply styles.\par
The disadvantages of External Style Sheets are:\par
- In order to import style information for each document, an extra download is needed.\par
- Until the external style sheet is loaded, it may not be possible to render the document.\par
- For small number of style definitions, it is not viable.\par
\par
\b\i0\fs32 17.What is the meaning of the CSS selector? \par
\b0\i\fs24 It is a pattern of elements and other terms that tell the browser which HTML elements should be selected to have the CSS property values inside the rule applied to them. The element or elements which are selected by the selector are referred to as the subject of the selector.\par
